
# BlackPixel

BlackPixel captures a full-page screenshot of a website and calculates the
percentage of pixels that are exactly black (`#000000`).

## Install

```powershell
npm install
```

## Analyze a Website

```powershell
npm run analyze -- https://your-website.com
```

You can also run the script directly:

```powershell
node black-pixel-analyzer.js https://your-website.com
```

Each run writes a local `page.png` screenshot so you can inspect what was
measured. The screenshot is ignored by git because it is generated output.
